WEBVTT

00:00:00.280 --> 00:00:02.159
I've been in the television production

00:00:02.159 --> 00:00:04.160
and creation business for the last 15

00:00:04.160 --> 00:00:06.680
years in Asia most of the shows that

00:00:06.680 --> 00:00:09.000
I've produced have been around music

00:00:09.000 --> 00:00:11.400
about celebrating and promoting Chinese

00:00:11.400 --> 00:00:13.719
artists I guess the motivation is

00:00:13.719 --> 00:00:15.240
because that very very early on I

00:00:15.240 --> 00:00:17.080
realized I really have the talent to be

00:00:17.080 --> 00:00:19.680
an artist myself so it was best that I

00:00:19.680 --> 00:00:21.279
get into the business of helping them to

00:00:21.279 --> 00:00:24.960
enable their dreams in 2003 I was given

00:00:24.960 --> 00:00:26.960
an opportunity to create and write a

00:00:26.960 --> 00:00:29.359
show that would eventually become one of

00:00:29.359 --> 00:00:31.599
the highest Prime Time Friday evening

00:00:31.599 --> 00:00:35.000
programs in China called Wasing show or

00:00:35.000 --> 00:00:37.800
in Chinese or in English called my

00:00:37.800 --> 00:00:42.120
show season 1 we had 5,000 people come

00:00:42.120 --> 00:00:46.399
in audition in season two we had 50,000

00:00:46.399 --> 00:00:48.760
people com in In audition and by season

00:00:48.760 --> 00:00:51.680
3 we had 150,000 people lined up across

00:00:51.680 --> 00:00:53.960
the country to audition and it's with

00:00:53.960 --> 00:00:55.960
that today I'd like to title my speech

00:00:55.960 --> 00:00:58.920
to be called dreams of Chinese Young

00:00:58.920 --> 00:01:00.440
artist

00:01:00.440 --> 00:01:03.840
by season two I guess I had become an

00:01:03.840 --> 00:01:06.760
accidental celebrity as part of the show

00:01:06.760 --> 00:01:09.119
boxes and boxes a fan mail came in

00:01:09.119 --> 00:01:12.000
flowers paintings t-shirts pillows etc

00:01:12.000 --> 00:01:15.600
etc pulled into my office and this was

00:01:15.600 --> 00:01:17.240
something I had actually hadn't

00:01:17.240 --> 00:01:19.560
completely expected but through the

00:01:19.560 --> 00:01:21.320
letters that they wrote and all the

00:01:21.320 --> 00:01:23.600
questions that they were asking us about

00:01:23.600 --> 00:01:25.640
I got a glimpse about Chinese young

00:01:25.640 --> 00:01:28.600
people and their dreams that was

00:01:28.600 --> 00:01:31.520
completely revolutionary or Revelation

00:01:31.520 --> 00:01:34.520
or a revelation to me so I'd like to

00:01:34.520 --> 00:01:37.320
share with you three stories about a boy

00:01:37.320 --> 00:01:40.680
from tundu a girl from Shang and then

00:01:40.680 --> 00:01:42.439
another boy from

00:01:42.439 --> 00:01:46.960
Ken janga came to the show in 2004 and

00:01:46.960 --> 00:01:49.079
his song was the back street Boy song

00:01:49.079 --> 00:01:52.240
called no matter what he sang it in

00:01:52.240 --> 00:01:54.880
perfect English and perfect diction

00:01:54.880 --> 00:01:56.799
afterwards I went up to him and I said

00:01:56.799 --> 00:01:58.399
so where did you learn to speak like

00:01:58.399 --> 00:02:00.600
that or sing like that he looked at me

00:02:00.600 --> 00:02:02.880
with a blank face and I realized that he

00:02:02.880 --> 00:02:05.520
didn't speak a word of English later on

00:02:05.520 --> 00:02:07.320
I realized that he had played a song

00:02:07.320 --> 00:02:09.599
over and over and over again in order to

00:02:09.599 --> 00:02:12.120
get his Pitch Perfect Right and perfect

00:02:12.120 --> 00:02:14.879
English his mother came to me with a bag

00:02:14.879 --> 00:02:17.920
of noodles with a well-worn white apron

00:02:17.920 --> 00:02:19.920
very very Brown from I guess years of

00:02:19.920 --> 00:02:21.959
working and I learned later that it was

00:02:21.959 --> 00:02:23.879
her mother who made a living by selling

00:02:23.879 --> 00:02:26.239
noodles on a roadside that supported his

00:02:26.239 --> 00:02:29.840
dreams of being a singer when Jang first

00:02:29.840 --> 00:02:31.920
started to want to sing he went to a

00:02:31.920 --> 00:02:34.440
local bar and the boss there said to him

00:02:34.440 --> 00:02:36.560
you can come and sing for 4 hours and

00:02:36.560 --> 00:02:39.680
I'll give you w five REM andb he looked

00:02:39.680 --> 00:02:41.440
at the Wai and he couldn't believe

00:02:41.440 --> 00:02:43.040
that's how much money he could make from

00:02:43.040 --> 00:02:45.840
singing with many many wuk he bought a

00:02:45.840 --> 00:02:47.959
computer downloaded more music and

00:02:47.959 --> 00:02:51.159
taught himself more English songs couple

00:02:51.159 --> 00:02:52.760
of months ago eight years later in

00:02:52.760 --> 00:02:55.200
Beijing I went to a concert at the

00:02:55.200 --> 00:02:57.680
people's Hall of people and he sang

00:02:57.680 --> 00:03:00.840
before 10,000 fans that were screaming

00:03:00.840 --> 00:03:02.319
and you shouldn't have seen you should

00:03:02.319 --> 00:03:04.840
have seen the smile on his mother's face

00:03:04.840 --> 00:03:07.720
she was so proud the second person I

00:03:07.720 --> 00:03:10.040
like to talk about is waying she's 21

00:03:10.040 --> 00:03:12.640
years old from Shenyang very very

00:03:12.640 --> 00:03:14.720
attractive low out toour voice came to

00:03:14.720 --> 00:03:17.200
the show and immediately captivated

00:03:17.200 --> 00:03:19.799
everybody and then started to make it to

00:03:19.799 --> 00:03:21.840
the final 10 when she got a phone call

00:03:21.840 --> 00:03:24.480
from her boyfriend who said if you want

00:03:24.480 --> 00:03:26.760
to save the show I will break up with

00:03:26.760 --> 00:03:28.680
you I don't want you to be in Show

00:03:28.680 --> 00:03:31.680
Business ing had a legitimate shot at

00:03:31.680 --> 00:03:34.720
winning and she was conflicted we left

00:03:34.720 --> 00:03:37.120
the decision to her but in the end she

00:03:37.120 --> 00:03:39.480
volunteered to leave the show and

00:03:39.480 --> 00:03:42.200
withdraw from the competition a couple

00:03:42.200 --> 00:03:44.319
of years later I saw her in Beijing and

00:03:44.319 --> 00:03:46.360
I said what happened how are you doing

00:03:46.360 --> 00:03:48.519
she said well I broke with my boyfriend

00:03:48.519 --> 00:03:50.640
a year later and I swear I'll never

00:03:50.640 --> 00:03:55.000
listen to a man's advice again I said go

00:03:55.000 --> 00:03:57.400
girlfriend the L story I'd like to share

00:03:57.400 --> 00:03:59.200
with you is about a gentleman who rode a

00:03:59.200 --> 00:04:02.640
horse for six hours to audition in tundu

00:04:02.640 --> 00:04:04.760
he sang a song that he used to sing to

00:04:04.760 --> 00:04:07.239
his sheeps and kongan as you know is

00:04:07.239 --> 00:04:10.200
famous for love music after singing this

00:04:10.200 --> 00:04:11.920
we gave him an immediate pass to

00:04:11.920 --> 00:04:15.079
Shanghai and he said no thank you but I

00:04:15.079 --> 00:04:17.759
have to go back and tend to my flock it

00:04:17.759 --> 00:04:19.479
turns out that he has never heard his

00:04:19.479 --> 00:04:22.440
voice recorded in digital form and as a

00:04:22.440 --> 00:04:25.040
result of his story and his passion for

00:04:25.040 --> 00:04:27.080
music We decided to make a small

00:04:27.080 --> 00:04:29.280
donation to Kong Den where there is now

00:04:29.280 --> 00:04:32.360
a small digital recording studio a

00:04:32.360 --> 00:04:34.240
couple of months later I started to get

00:04:34.240 --> 00:04:36.000
lots and lots of thank you letters from

00:04:36.000 --> 00:04:38.440
around the country apparently from Gansu

00:04:38.440 --> 00:04:41.680
chinai and Tibet and there the people

00:04:41.680 --> 00:04:43.199
started to thank me about all these

00:04:43.199 --> 00:04:45.160
things that I was supposedly donating

00:04:45.160 --> 00:04:47.199
school supplies socker ball sneakers

00:04:47.199 --> 00:04:49.280
clothing and so forth I actually didn't

00:04:49.280 --> 00:04:50.560
do any of this and I was quite

00:04:50.560 --> 00:04:52.800
embarrassed and I started to deny doing

00:04:52.800 --> 00:04:54.680
all of this but as you know in Chinese

00:04:54.680 --> 00:04:56.160
culture the more you deny it the more

00:04:56.160 --> 00:04:57.360
they really believe you're just being

00:04:57.360 --> 00:04:59.320
modest so they kept saying Yeah right

00:04:59.320 --> 00:05:01.440
sure sure but you know thank you anyway

00:05:01.440 --> 00:05:03.479
but apparently what I realized was that

00:05:03.479 --> 00:05:06.039
the fans had taken my name and started

00:05:06.039 --> 00:05:08.600
to make donations on behalf of my

00:05:08.600 --> 00:05:10.919
nickname and it was a movement that I

00:05:10.919 --> 00:05:13.000
guess they had embraced all their own

00:05:13.000 --> 00:05:15.080
and that really taught me a great deal

00:05:15.080 --> 00:05:17.919
about what celebrity and fame is about

00:05:17.919 --> 00:05:19.800
and so through this story of three

00:05:19.800 --> 00:05:22.840
people one who made it Against All Odds

00:05:22.840 --> 00:05:25.240
a girl who had to change her Traditional

00:05:25.240 --> 00:05:27.520
Values and rules in the face of

00:05:27.520 --> 00:05:30.000
competition and lastly some somebody who

00:05:30.000 --> 00:05:33.120
resisted the fast urbanization of China

00:05:33.120 --> 00:05:35.199
decided to go back to his own ways I

00:05:35.199 --> 00:05:37.639
have three very very quick and simple

00:05:37.639 --> 00:05:40.360
reflection the first is that I guess we

00:05:40.360 --> 00:05:42.000
really should be good stewards of what

00:05:42.000 --> 00:05:45.160
we've been given do really the most of

00:05:45.160 --> 00:05:49.080
what you have more or less the second

00:05:49.080 --> 00:05:50.840
thing is Andy wo once said that

00:05:50.840 --> 00:05:53.199
everybody's going to have 15 minutes of

00:05:53.199 --> 00:05:56.840
fame I'm clearly on my 14th minute and

00:05:56.840 --> 00:05:59.600
I've learned that really with Fame so so

00:05:59.600 --> 00:06:02.280
much of it is about it could be warmth

00:06:02.280 --> 00:06:04.720
and provide Comfort or it could destroy

00:06:04.720 --> 00:06:06.880
everything around you luckily in this

00:06:06.880 --> 00:06:08.880
case the young people around the show

00:06:08.880 --> 00:06:11.280
has taught me a lot about what it can do

00:06:11.280 --> 00:06:13.720
for the greater good last but not least

00:06:13.720 --> 00:06:16.639
my final thought is that I think there

00:06:16.639 --> 00:06:19.000
is a creative Renaissance going on in

00:06:19.000 --> 00:06:21.840
China today young people are creating

00:06:21.840 --> 00:06:24.880
things online musically fashion artwork

00:06:24.880 --> 00:06:28.479
and so forth at a pace and a sense that

00:06:28.479 --> 00:06:31.199
I would Define as modernity inspired by

00:06:31.199 --> 00:06:33.440
tradition they're redefining for

00:06:33.440 --> 00:06:35.960
themselves what modern China is and I

00:06:35.960 --> 00:06:38.840
hope that as I continue to do television

00:06:38.840 --> 00:06:40.400
that I would be able to bring and share

00:06:40.400 --> 00:06:42.840
more of these stories with all of you

00:06:42.840 --> 00:06:45.479
because it's really happening every day

00:06:45.479 --> 00:06:49.160
all around us thank you very

00:06:49.199 --> 00:06:52.199
much
